               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-1137" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1137" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1137" type="surname" value="GRIPPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1137" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD GRIPPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a wharfinger. The prisoner was in my service—he had no authority to take peas—I believe these split peas (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>) to be mine.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-1138" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1138" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1138" type="surname" value="RICHARDS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-1138" type="given" value="MORRISS"></interp>MORRISS RICHARDS</persName>
                  </hi>. On 5th Nov., between nine 3nd ten o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner coming with-his son from Mr. Gripper's ware-house with this bundle under the boy's arm—I asked where he got it—he said his father gave it him—the father was not there then—I went to him, and asked if the boy was his son—he said, "Yes"—I asked if he gave him those peas—he said, "Yes"—I asked if his master allowed him to do so—he said, "Yes"—I took him and the peas.</p>
